</span></span><b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
color:black'>Compartment&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>syndrome is an
extremely dangerous and serious condition that occurs as a result of
compression of the muscles of the forearm against the background of fractures
or severe bruises;&nbsp;the main symptom is severe pain, which is inadequate to
the severity of the injury;&nbsp;requires urgent surgical intervention;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:
normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;color:black'>·<span
